myBirths78<-Births78 %>% rename(Wday = wday)
head(myBirths78)
##         date births dayofyear  Wday
## 1 1978-01-01   7701         1   Sun
## 2 1978-01-02   7527         2   Mon
## 3 1978-01-03   8825         3  Tues
## 4 1978-01-04   8859         4   Wed
## 5 1978-01-05   9043         5 Thurs
## 6 1978-01-06   9208         6   Fri
avg_Births<-myBirths78 %>%
  group_by(Month = month(date, label = TRUE), Wday) %>%
  summarise(avg = mean(births))
head(avg_Births)
## Source: local data frame [6 x 3]
## Groups: Month [1]
## 
##   Month  Wday     avg
##   <ord> <ord>   <dbl>
## 1   Jan   Sun 7634.00
## 2   Jan   Mon 8918.60
## 3   Jan  Tues 9164.20
## 4   Jan   Wed 9069.75
## 5   Jan Thurs 9228.75
## 6   Jan   Fri 9158.50
plot1 <- avg_Births %>%
  ggplot(aes(x= Wday, y= avg)) + geom_point(aes(col = Month))
plot1

Holidays <- read.csv("http://tiny.cc/dcf/US-Holidays.csv") %>%
mutate(date = lubridate::dmy(date))
head(Holidays)
##          holiday       date year
## 1 New Year's Day 1978-01-01 1978
## 2 New Year's Day 1979-01-01 1979
## 3 New Year's Day 1980-01-01 1980
## 4 New Year's Day 1981-01-01 1981
## 5 New Year's Day 1982-01-01 1982
## 6 New Year's Day 1983-01-01 1983
year_wanted <- "1978"
holiday_wanted <- c(11, 12)
myHolidays <- Holidays %>%
  filter(year %in% year_wanted, month(date) %in% holiday_wanted)
head(myHolidays)
##            holiday       date year
## 1    Veteran's Day 1978-11-11 1978
## 2 Thanksgiving Day 1978-11-23 1978
## 3    Christmas Day 1978-12-25 1978
plot2 <- avg_Births %>%
  ggplot(aes(x= Wday, y= avg)) + geom_point(aes(col = Month))
plot2 <- plot2 + geom_vline(xintercept = wday(myHolidays$date), data = myHolidays)
plot2

plot3 <- plot2 + geom_text(data = myHolidays, aes(x=wday(myHolidays$date), y=8000, label = holiday), size = 3, angle=65)
plot3

avg <- Births78 %>% 
  summarise(avg=mean(births))
avg
##        avg
## 1 9132.162
plot4 <- plot3 + geom_hline( yintercept = as.numeric(avg))
plot4

plot4 + annotate("text", label="avg", x = "Sun", y = 9000)
